    <p><strong>An exhaust fan for a commercial kitchen is not a luxury — it is the backbone of a safe, legal, and productive food business in India.</strong> Whether you are setting up a cloud kitchen in Bengaluru, a biryani restaurant in Hyderabad, or a hotel banquet kitchen in Delhi, your ventilation system determines everything from staff comfort and fire safety to FSSAI licence approval and pollution NOC clearance. Yet most food business owners in India underbudget ventilation, treat it as an afterthought, and end up with kitchens that overheat, accumulate grease, and fail inspections.</p>

    <p>This 2026 guide covers the full commercial kitchen ventilation ecosystem: exhaust hoods (wall-mount, island, proximity), exhaust fans (centrifugal, axial, inline), ductwork design, make-up air systems, grease traps, fire suppression integration, HVAC coordination, CFM calculations, pollution NOC requirements, price tables, top brands, installation best practices, and a maintenance schedule that keeps your system safe and compliant. Every price and specification reflects the current Indian market — not Western benchmarks that do not apply here.</p>

    <p>If you are looking only for exhaust hood types and sizing, see our focused <a href="/blog/commercial-exhaust-hood">commercial exhaust hood guide</a>. This article takes a broader view — the complete ventilation system from intake to exhaust discharge, including the grease management and regulatory components most guides ignore.</p>

