    <h3>Grease Trap Sizing</h3>
    <p>Size your grease trap based on wastewater flow rate, not kitchen size. The standard formula: Flow Rate (litres per minute) x Retention Time (minutes) = Minimum Trap Capacity. For most Indian commercial kitchens, retention time should be 2–4 minutes. A 50-cover restaurant with a 3-compartment sink flowing at 20 LPM needs a minimum 60-litre trap (20 x 3 = 60). Over-sizing by 25% is recommended to account for peak loads.</p>

    <h3>Maintenance Schedule</h3>
    <p>Grease traps must be cleaned regularly — weekly for high-volume kitchens (deep fryers, tandoors), fortnightly for moderate volumes. A neglected grease trap overflows, causing sewer backups, pest infestations, and foul odours. Many municipalities now fine commercial kitchens for overflowing or non-functional grease traps. Maintain a cleaning log for FSSAI and municipal inspections.</p>

